text: Habersham County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, 46,031 people lived there. The county seat is Clarkesville. It is named for Joseph Habersham, a slave owner and veteran of the American War for Independence. == Communities == === Cities === * Alto * Baldwin * Clarkesville * Cornelia * Demorest * Mount Airy * Tallulah Falls === Census-designated place === * Raoul === Other unincorporated communities === * Batesville * Habersham Mills * Hollywood * Turnerville == References == Category:1818 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
